{
  "texts": [
    "One such metric for evaluating the realism of SDs include \"fidelity\" that measures the structural similarity between original and synthetic images [36].",
    "BiasesDespite the advantage of reduced biases associated with SDs, generative models can still retain some of the biases [36].",
    "Since humans are involved in the production of synthetic data, the inherent risk of incorporating human bias remains an area of concern.",
    "Similar to \"provider bias\" where a physician may be prejudiced against a certain racial group for example, these biases invariably translate into AI models [36].",
    "If these biases are not addressed at an early stage of AI development, it can lead to inaccurate results that are not representative of the population [37]."
  ]
}